    ('CLAS-C 311', 'CLASSICAL EPICS', '29420', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'LH 101', 'Kenneth Draper', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'LINDLEY HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The development of Greek and Latin epic from the rich oral tradition of Homer to the strictly literary form exemplified by Vergil''s Aeneid. Epic masterpieces are read with reference to relevant historical and archaeological background.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
