    ('CSCI-A 310', 'PROBLEM SOLVING USING DATA', '10490', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'JH 124', 'Dan-Adrian German', 44, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'BIOLOGY BUILDING', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course introduces algorithms and data structures for solving real world problems using data. Topics include: searching and sorting, basic data structures (heaps, hash tables, binary search and splay trees etc.), concepts of algorithm design (e.g., divide-and-conquer, dynamic programming), graph algorithms and clustering.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
